# Allowlist .gitignore — ignore everything by default, then explicitly allow.
#
# When a new directory or file should land in the repo, add it here as a !-rule.
# Structural additions are deliberate operator decisions, not defaults.
# This prevents agents from accidentally committing throwaway files, secrets,
# concurrent-session scratch, or anything outside the documented structure.
#
# Discipline: if `git add <path>` refuses with "ignored by .gitignore",
# stop and ask: should this go in the repo, and if yes, should the
# allowlist grow to admit it (one-line edit) or should the path be revised
# to fit the existing structure?

# ---- Step 1: ignore everything ----
*

# ---- Step 2: allow this file itself ----
!.gitignore

# ---- Step 3: root-level files ----
!CLAUDE.md
!README.md

# ---- Step 4: .claude/ — Anthropic-documented project slots ----
# Per-session reasoning artifacts produced by the 13-step workflow are tracked
# as a longitudinal human-facing record (drift detection, growth vs regression
# analysis over time). The AI is not instructed to read prior sessions — its
# perspective remains ephemeral scratchpad.
# Do NOT prune for noise: low-value sessions are diagnostic data.
# Periodic sweeps should be for PRIVACY REDACTION only (scrub pasted-in
# proprietary names from other repos), not deletion.
# See .claude/session-artifacts/README.md for the lifecycle.
#
# Runtime caches (.claude/.metrics/, .claude/worktrees/, and the various
# Anthropic-managed caches like agent-memory-local/, backups/, debug/,
# file-history/, image-cache/, paste-cache/, projects/, session-env/,
# shell-snapshots/, tasks/, todos/) are NOT allowlisted — they stay ignored
# as intended. Only checked-in slots Anthropic documents are tracked.
!.claude/
.claude/*
!.claude/README.md
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/agents/**
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/commands/**
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/**
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/hooks/**
!.claude/session-artifacts/
!.claude/session-artifacts/**
!.claude/rules/
!.claude/rules/**
!.claude/agent-memory/
!.claude/agent-memory/**
!.claude/output-styles/
!.claude/output-styles/**
!.claude/plugins/
!.claude/plugins/**
# Per-session local-only files (e.g. absolute target-repo path written by `critique-prep`).
# Re-ignored after the broad allow above — committed artifacts must never contain
# absolute paths (path discipline per CLAUDE.md). The .local/ subdir is the only
# place an absolute path is allowed to live, and only on the operator's machine.
.claude/session-artifacts/*/.local/
!.claude/settings.json
# .claude/settings.local.json deliberately NOT allowed (per-developer override
# — domain allowlist, Bash permissions, etc.). The shared settings.json IS tracked.

# ---- Step 5: canon/ — manifest + ingest scripts + corpus inventory ----
# Ingested canon text bodies (source.txt) are regenerated by bin/ingest-canon.py
# or populated from local plaintext via bin/ingest-owned-book.py — excluded
# below. The rest of canon/corpus/ (stubs, citation.yaml, README.md) IS tracked
# so the corpus inventory is visible in git.
#
# Schema_version 2 (2026-05-17): the single source of truth is canon/sources.yaml.
# The previous canon/sources.ingest.yaml was eliminated in the SSOT rewrite —
# the ingester reads sources.yaml directly.
!canon/
canon/*
!canon/README.md
!canon/sources.yaml
!canon/refresh-feeds.yaml
!canon/corpus/
!canon/corpus/**
canon/corpus/*/source.txt

# ---- Step 6: upgrades/ — the R&D lab. Only the four documented tier folders. ----
# Adding a new tier requires a deliberate edit to this allowlist.
!upgrades/
upgrades/*
!upgrades/README.md
!upgrades/LEDGER.md
!upgrades/no-brainer/
!upgrades/no-brainer/**
!upgrades/normal/
!upgrades/normal/**
!upgrades/outlandish/
!upgrades/outlandish/**
!upgrades/profound/
!upgrades/profound/**

# ---- Step 7: bin/ — repo-wide scripts ----
!bin/
!bin/**

# ---- Step 8: plans/ — ephemeral session scratchpad ----
# See plans/README.md. Tracked-but-cleaned: commit if value, delete when work lands.
!plans/
!plans/**

# ---- Step 9: prompts/ — working/historical prompts (paste-into-external-tool briefs) ----
# See prompts/README.md. Not a Claude Code primitive; ignored everywhere else.
!prompts/
!prompts/**

# ---- Step 10: research/ — SOTA distillations (dated, tiered) ----
# See research/README.md for the index. Each distillation carries Vintage /
# Next-review-by metadata. Superseded files stay on disk for audit.
!research/
!research/**

# ---- Step 11: maintenance/ — repo-hygiene zone (sibling to upgrades/) ----
# See maintenance/README.md. Workflow is blind to maintenance; this is operator-triggered only.
!maintenance/
!maintenance/**

# ---- Step 12: .genesis/ — founding documents (initial-commit material) ----
# Hidden by .-prefix; not active workflow surface; preserved as historical seed.
# See .genesis/README.md.
!.genesis/
!.genesis/**

# ---- macOS noise: explicit (already covered by Step 1, but explicit for clarity) ----
.DS_Store
